16:59.250 --> 17:03.516
And, you! Don't act like
you not seeing someone!

17:03.550 --> 17:05.108
I know you!

17:05.150 --> 17:09.086
Sneakin' outta here,
making calls all the time.

17:09.120 --> 17:12.521
You're not slick.
( laughing )

17:12.560 --> 17:14.755
Uh-uh.
Uh-uh!

17:14.800 --> 17:16.756
I knew it.
I knew it!

17:16.800 --> 17:19.598
Who is it?
Come on!

17:21.470 --> 17:23.267
Is it a boy or girl?

17:25.210 --> 17:28.634
Lord, I thought
that was a college phase.

17:31.110 --> 17:33.544
It's what's within.

17:33.580 --> 17:35.218
Not the package.

17:35.250 --> 17:37.810
I ain't gonna lie,
I love Hollywood's package.

17:37.850 --> 17:39.738
Charley:
Okay. All right.

17:39.790 --> 17:41.815
We're talking about Nova!

17:41.860 --> 17:44.226
Charley:
Come on, we're waiting!

17:49.600 --> 17:57.837
- Morning, Remy.
- Morning, Charley.

17:57.870 --> 17:59.565
Just you today?

17:59.610 --> 18:01.430
No Ralph Angel?

18:01.480 --> 18:03.402
I'm back now.

18:03.450 --> 18:04.849
( chuckles )
Okay.

18:04.880 --> 18:06.438
You up for all this?

18:06.480 --> 18:07.617
Let's do it, yeah?

18:20.330 --> 18:23.663
So, how much
for a good tractor?

18:23.700 --> 18:24.689
$200,000.

18:24.730 --> 18:27.130
What?

18:27.170 --> 18:28.694
For a tractor?

18:28.740 --> 18:30.605
That's the cost
of a Tesla.

18:30.640 --> 18:32.460
Yeah, that's brand new.

18:32.510 --> 18:34.705
If you play your cards right
at the auction,

18:34.740 --> 18:37.607
you should be able to get
what you need for half that.

18:37.650 --> 18:39.379
What about the seed cane?

18:39.410 --> 18:41.742
And the migrant workers,
the farm managers?

18:41.780 --> 18:44.783
And we still gotta weed out
what's already been planted.

18:44.820 --> 18:47.687
Let's just take it
one step at a time, okay?

18:47.720 --> 18:49.756
The good news?

18:49.790 --> 18:51.678
This here's good land.

18:51.730 --> 18:54.255
Just needs tending.

18:54.300 --> 18:55.619
Listen,

18:55.660 --> 18:58.629
you can tell because
the dirt's still sweet.

19:00.500 --> 19:01.762
Hmm.

19:01.800 --> 19:03.461
Taste it.

19:13.820 --> 19:16.277
Don't eat that!

19:16.320 --> 19:17.719
I just wanted to see
if you'd do it.

19:17.750 --> 19:20.253
You what?

19:20.290 --> 19:23.726
Hey, you remember
Prosper Denton,
from the meeting?

19:24.890 --> 19:26.357
Remy,

19:26.390 --> 19:29.655
now, you got me out here
away from my fishing line.

19:29.700 --> 19:31.668
- Let's get to it.
- Right.

19:31.700 --> 19:33.691
So, Charley, um...

19:33.740 --> 19:36.538
you need a farm manager
and I think that Prosper's
the man for the job.

19:36.570 --> 19:38.561
- The problem is--
- I don't want the job.

19:38.610 --> 19:41.909
I don't need the job.
Look, I'm retired, okay?

19:41.940 --> 19:44.408
Well, thank you
for considering it.

19:44.450 --> 19:46.941
Who said
I'm considering it?

19:46.980 --> 19:49.471
He's here
as a favor to me.

19:51.920 --> 19:53.888
( sighs )

19:53.920 --> 19:55.751
Um...

19:55.790 --> 19:58.327
So, how many
acres you plannin' on
the first rotation?

19:58.360 --> 19:59.679
300.

19:59.730 --> 20:02.392
That's too much land to handle
for a small cane farmer,

20:02.430 --> 20:05.524
especially one late
getting started out.

20:05.570 --> 20:07.788
Make it 200 acres
instead of 300.

20:07.840 --> 20:11.401
Okay, 200 acres.

20:11.440 --> 20:13.635
You talking to somebody else?
What do they call that?

20:13.680 --> 20:15.978
- Texting.
- I'm not-- I'm not
texting, Mr. Prosper.

20:16.010 --> 20:17.773
It's just--
I'm taking notes.

20:17.810 --> 20:20.449
'Cause I was about to say,
I can go fishing
if you're busy.

20:20.480 --> 20:23.278
The only one
I'm talking to is you.

20:25.590 --> 20:26.682
( sighs )

20:26.720 --> 20:29.359
( phone ringing )

20:31.960 --> 20:34.690
Bordelon, here you go.

20:34.730 --> 20:36.493
Appreciate that.

20:41.470 --> 20:44.030
Mr. Earl,
this ain't right.

20:44.070 --> 20:45.958
My check's short.

20:46.010 --> 20:48.433
I worked 40,
but this for 32.

20:48.480 --> 20:50.471
No, that's about right.

20:51.910 --> 20:54.777
About right?
Check's short, bruh.

20:54.820 --> 20:57.288
I said it ain't short.

20:57.320 --> 21:00.357
You've been inside,
so maybe you forgot.

21:00.390 --> 21:02.608
Freedom ain't free, bro.

21:02.660 --> 21:04.787
You know what I mean?

21:15.770 --> 21:17.533
Hey...

21:17.570 --> 21:19.868
welcome to life
after prison, man.

21:23.350 --> 21:25.705
So, now that you see
how it is around here,

21:25.750 --> 21:27.377
how you gonna roll?

21:27.420 --> 21:29.615
Got a little boy
who need to eat,

21:29.650 --> 21:32.949
a parole officer
who don't give a damn
about nothing but a stub.

21:32.990 --> 21:34.912
I'll make do
till I can do better.

21:34.960 --> 21:36.757
You can be
doing better
right now.

21:36.790 --> 21:38.985
Let me make
that bad stalk
up to you, man.

21:39.030 --> 21:40.895
Look, we did our time,
right?

21:40.930 --> 21:41.919
How much longer
we gotta do?

21:41.960 --> 21:43.496
Till we die?

21:43.530 --> 21:45.919
Man, they can all
kiss my ass.

21:45.970 --> 21:48.063
What you talking about?

21:48.100 --> 21:50.364
They take,
we take back.

21:51.610 --> 21:54.408
Look, shipment come in,
right?

21:54.440 --> 21:57.341
You go into the order record,
you change the number
of the units ordered.

21:57.380 --> 22:00.474
Right?
Bam-- we keep the extra.

22:00.520 --> 22:02.374
I got a hook up dude
on the other end.

22:02.420 --> 22:04.547
He change it on his side,
make it look clean.

22:04.590 --> 22:07.787
Dawg, and my baby
still got shoes.

22:07.820 --> 22:10.380
- Are you down?
- No.

22:10.430 --> 22:13.456
Thanks, but I'm cool.

22:13.500 --> 22:15.923
- You have
a good day, Effie Mae.
- Thank you.

22:15.960 --> 22:17.723
( music playing )

22:20.970 --> 22:22.961
Is there a problem,
Vance?

22:23.000 --> 22:25.434
You shorted that lady $5.

22:25.470 --> 22:29.099
Are you stealing, Violet?
Or you can't count?

22:29.140 --> 22:31.074
The lady's name
is Effie Mae.

22:31.110 --> 22:33.374
_ Eff_ie Mae
is on a fixed income.

22:33.420 --> 22:35.638
She owed $3
from her last bill.

22:35.680 --> 22:38.945
I kept $5 today to pay
for the $3 that she owed.

22:38.990 --> 22:41.618
Plus, she gave a dollar
to the High Yellow
as a thank you

22:41.660 --> 22:44.857
and _one to me
for being graCIous.

22:44.890 --> 22:48.792
Well, I'm still
gonna have to talk to
my Uncle Clive about this.

22:48.830 --> 22:51.060
( laughing )

22:51.100 --> 22:53.967
Now, you see,

22:54.000 --> 22:57.037
graciousness is something
you clearly know nothing about.

22:57.070 --> 22:59.766
But, that's okay,

22:59.810 --> 23:03.849
'cause I'm gonna show you
some graciousness today

23:03.880 --> 23:05.609
by saving your life.

23:05.650 --> 23:07.470
Because if_I have
to stay up in here,

23:07.520 --> 23:09.647
I will absolutely kill

23:09.680 --> 23:12.444
your little
narrow-minded ass.

23:13.690 --> 23:14.714
I quit.

23:17.730 --> 23:20.119
- Do you want more?
- I'll take whatever you got.

23:20.160 --> 23:22.651
You must be running low
on customers, huh?

23:22.700 --> 23:25.168
'Cause you ain't never
agreed to give me this much
all at one time.

23:25.200 --> 23:28.897
Don't look a gift horse
in the mouth, Rid.

23:28.940 --> 23:31.932
You know, Dee's taking up
a collection for Too Sweet.

23:31.970 --> 23:33.528
You should get in
on that.

23:33.580 --> 23:36.572
That's the least
I could do.

23:36.610 --> 23:38.498
I mean, you know,
when he got popped,

23:38.550 --> 23:40.177
he had one
of my spliffs on him.

23:40.210 --> 23:41.973
And I felt bad,
you know?

23:43.690 --> 23:45.646
You sold my stuff
to Too Sweet?

23:45.690 --> 23:48.887
Yeah, Nova.
We all get our shit
from you.

23:51.930 --> 23:54.592
Leave.

23:54.630 --> 23:55.858
Now.

24:06.570 --> 24:09.676
( car engine starts )

24:09.710 --> 24:12.975
Nova, your name
is on the lips of every cop
in this precinct.

24:13.010 --> 24:14.568
You're not gonna
shut me out.

24:14.620 --> 24:16.713
We're gonna talk
about this, damn it.

24:19.720 --> 24:22.086
You want to take on
this whole system
with your article?

24:22.120 --> 24:25.851
The whole system
all because of one boy
who broke the law.

24:28.300 --> 24:30.825
This whole system
you're talking about,

24:30.870 --> 24:34.033
it's built and funded
on the backs of black bodies.

24:34.070 --> 24:35.594
Here we go again.

24:35.640 --> 24:37.699
Oh, you have
a problem with me
speaking my truth now?

24:37.740 --> 24:39.230
I'm on your side
and you know it.

24:39.270 --> 24:40.737
Are you?

24:42.710 --> 24:45.907
Because I'm just
getting started, Calvin.

24:45.950 --> 24:49.579
This article is going to be
the first of a series
that exposes

24:49.620 --> 24:52.987
the corruption
in New Orleans.

24:53.020 --> 24:55.488
All because of one kid?

24:58.690 --> 25:01.796
_ One kid
is one too many,
Calvin.

25:04.030 --> 25:06.169
Too Sweet is hurt

25:06.200 --> 25:09.089
andinjaH
because the system

25:09.140 --> 25:10.664
said he should be.

25:13.980 --> 25:16.778
You ever met a white kid
nicknamed "Too Sweet"?

25:18.980 --> 25:21.175
No.

25:21.220 --> 25:24.610
Because it's so damn rare
that a black boy
makes it through

25:24.650 --> 25:26.743
with their_ soul
in one piece

25:26.790 --> 25:28.883
that he get a nickname...

25:30.260 --> 25:32.558
just for pulling it off.

25:38.370 --> 25:40.520
I love you.

25:42.100 --> 25:43.931
But you are
such a hypocrite.

25:45.940 --> 25:48.773
You pedal drugs
to people you claim
to want to save.

25:48.810 --> 25:51.074
You need to calm down.
It's just weed.

25:51.110 --> 25:53.578
And it's still illegal.

25:56.850 --> 25:58.044
Get out.

26:01.220 --> 26:02.881
Now.

26:10.830 --> 26:13.162
You know, a part of me
always wondered why
you picked me,

26:13.200 --> 26:14.963
a white, married cop.

26:17.340 --> 26:20.639
I got it.

26:20.680 --> 26:23.877
You never _
wanted a relationship,
you just wanted company.

26:23.910 --> 26:27.710
And don't walk out that door
without leaving your key.

26:50.370 --> 26:51.200
- ( chatter)
- ( mu5ic playing )

26:58.980 --> 27:02.108
* Take it slow, baby

27:02.150 --> 27:08.988
* It pulls to my heart...

27:09.020 --> 27:11.750
Charley:
Looks like the land
that time forgot around here.

27:11.790 --> 27:15.328
- ( laughs ) Brother.
- Hey, how you doin'?

27:15.360 --> 27:18.158
Nice to see you again,
Mr. Denton.

27:20.840 --> 27:23.866
No matter what,
you just stick to your goals.

27:23.910 --> 27:27.368
A good tractor,
a five row cultivator,
a harvester...

27:27.410 --> 27:30.629
Get out of here for 200K
and you done done something.

27:32.450 --> 27:35.271
* That's why
it will lead you astray... *

27:35.320 --> 27:37.117
Yeah, see how it goes.

27:37.150 --> 27:39.744
Samuel:
Ms. Charley?

27:39.790 --> 27:41.257
I heard you came back.

27:41.290 --> 27:43.850
You sound surprised.

27:43.890 --> 27:45.426
All that fuss
in California,

27:45.460 --> 27:48.190
most ladies couldn't
get out of bed.

27:48.230 --> 27:51.028
- I'm not most ladies.
- I can see that...

27:51.070 --> 27:52.799
by the very fact
that you're here.

27:54.070 --> 27:55.469
Excuse me?

27:55.500 --> 27:57.263
You don't see
many women here

27:57.300 --> 27:59.200
trying to buy
tractor equipment,
do you?

28:01.110 --> 28:02.475
Come to think of it,

28:02.510 --> 28:05.070
there's not many
of your kind of folk
here neither.

28:05.110 --> 28:06.907
Ain't that right,
Prosper?

28:09.080 --> 28:11.287
Good luck on getting
what you need.

28:11.320 --> 28:13.413
Remy:
Forget him.
He's trouble.

28:13.450 --> 28:16.715
- Hey, sweet darling.
- Hi, Aunt Vi.

28:16.760 --> 28:17.920
Remy:
Hey.

28:19.090 --> 28:21.126
Have you seen Ralph Angel?

28:21.160 --> 28:24.197
_ If he's so interested
in getting Daddy's tractor
back, where is he?

28:24.230 --> 28:26.391
He's coming from work.
He'll be here.

28:27.840 --> 28:29.262
( gavel bangs )

28:29.300 --> 28:31.165
All right, ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the farm sale.

28:31.210 --> 28:33.770
Ladies and gentlemen,
we have a lot of good tractors
here today,

28:33.810 --> 28:35.732
and we've got the first one
right up here, first item.

28:35.780 --> 28:38.248
IH-9 will be your first lot.
And I mean...

28:38.280 --> 28:40.373
( horn blares )

28:52.360 --> 28:55.295
* I'm going down

28:55.330 --> 28:59.869
* I'm going down, down,
down, down, down *

29:03.340 --> 29:06.969
* Yes, I'm going down

29:07.010 --> 29:10.776
* I'm going down, down,
down, down, down *

29:14.880 --> 29:18.486
* Yes, I got my big feet
in the window *

