* Got my head
on the ground... *

29:24.290 --> 29:26.781
I have $95,000 here,
95, now to 100.

29:26.830 --> 29:28.422
( continues )

29:28.460 --> 29:30.860
$100,000, thank you.
I have $100,000...

29:30.900 --> 29:34.199
Now, 10, 110...
Okay, I've got 110 here
to the man with the tan.

29:34.240 --> 29:36.094
How about 115?
15-- 15-- gonna do it?

29:36.140 --> 29:37.539
Hit 15.
How about 115?

29:37.570 --> 29:39.128
Don't bid on that.

29:39.170 --> 29:41.172
You said the cultivator's
a good buy at 125.

29:41.210 --> 29:42.871
It's strategy.

29:42.910 --> 29:46.448
Now 20, 20.
I gotcha at 120, $120.
How about 125?

29:46.480 --> 29:49.278
Hit 25, hit 25,
25 anywhere?

29:49.320 --> 29:50.878
How about 125?
Thank you.

29:50.920 --> 29:53.514
How about 125, now 130.
( continues )

29:53.550 --> 29:56.257
Now_ 30? Now 30? Now 30?
Gomg once, now twme...

29:56.290 --> 30:00.386
- No.
- I sold a tractor
right there, $125,000,

30:00.430 --> 30:02.057
to the man
with the tan.

30:02.100 --> 30:03.624
I got here
quick as I could.

30:03.660 --> 30:06.128
Auctioneer:
All right, ladies and
gentlemen, right over here.

30:06.170 --> 30:08.866
- IH-15 will be
your next lot...
- That's Pop's tractor.

30:08.900 --> 30:10.458
Auctioneer:
Oh, boy, you talk about

30:10.500 --> 30:12.331
a bread and butter kind
of a tractor right there.

30:12.370 --> 30:15.134
There's a tiller
coming up next,
takes priority.

30:15.180 --> 30:17.535
So we ain't even gonna try?

30:17.580 --> 30:19.445
Aunt Vi!

30:19.480 --> 30:21.869
Baby, maybe we should
try to get your daddy's
tractor back.

30:21.920 --> 30:23.569
There are better_ tractors
at better prices.

30:23.620 --> 30:26.441
$2,500? How about $25,000,
what do you think?

30:26.490 --> 30:29.311
Okay, $25,000...
( continuing )

30:29.360 --> 30:30.884
I'll be back.

30:32.990 --> 30:36.357
You hang in there.
I'll be right back, okay?
I gotta call Hollywood.

30:36.400 --> 30:39.198
Auctioneer:
Right there, $35,000.
Thank you, sir.

30:39.230 --> 30:40.322
All right,
ladies and gentlemen...

30:40.370 --> 30:43.089
Let me help you,
let me help you.

30:43.140 --> 30:45.199
There you go.

30:45.240 --> 30:46.559
There you go.

30:48.240 --> 30:50.071
Mm-mm, mm-mm.
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

30:50.110 --> 30:51.600
- No, no, Leanne.
You gotta stop.
- Oh, come on.

30:51.650 --> 30:53.345
Hollywood, come on.
Come on.

30:53.380 --> 30:55.348
- No.
- Like we used to.

30:55.380 --> 30:57.268
I know you got love for me.

30:57.320 --> 30:58.947
I wanna make another baby.

30:58.990 --> 31:01.049
You just need
your medication,
that's all.

31:01.090 --> 31:02.114
Okay?

31:09.260 --> 31:12.627
( laughs )
You too good for me?

31:12.670 --> 31:17.232
Oh, come on, now.
You can-- you can
come closer.

31:17.270 --> 31:19.568
Oh, no, I can't.

31:19.610 --> 31:24.377
Now, you know
Leanne and Hollywood
ain't no more.

31:24.410 --> 31:27.641
You say it and...
( snaps fingers )

31:27.680 --> 31:29.238
that's it?

31:29.280 --> 31:30.474
Make it so?

31:30.520 --> 31:32.886
( phone ringing )

31:40.130 --> 31:42.394
Hey! Leanne,
give me my phone back.

31:42.430 --> 31:44.489
Who the hell is Vi?

31:44.530 --> 31:47.363
- Just give me
the phone back, okay?
- ( laughing )

31:52.140 --> 31:54.301
( Leanne laughing )

31:54.340 --> 31:56.638
Oh, come on.

32:05.750 --> 32:06.614
( beeps )

32:06.650 --> 32:10.188
Hey, baby,
where are you?

32:17.500 --> 32:20.594
Auctioneer: All right,
ladies and gentlemen,
last tractor we have today.

32:20.630 --> 32:22.530
I want you to pay attention
and look real close.

32:22.570 --> 32:26.438
It is a John Deere
7000 Series Harvester.

32:26.470 --> 32:29.075
They're hard to find.
They cost something
when you find them.

32:29.110 --> 32:32.102
Here's a good tractor.
This is a little
different story.

32:32.150 --> 32:34.448
_ We've been
selling a lot of tractors
and I'll tell you what,

32:34.480 --> 32:36.038
that's a farming machine
right there.

32:36.080 --> 32:37.308
And how many dollars here?

32:37.350 --> 32:40.979
I have a $200,000 bid
right here on it.

32:41.020 --> 32:43.181
$200,000, I want 210.

32:43.220 --> 32:45.450
210, how about 215?
( continues )

32:45.490 --> 32:47.685
$215...
( continues )

32:47.730 --> 32:50.221
25, 25, 25!

32:50.260 --> 32:52.467
Ma'am,
you gotta beat 250.

32:52.500 --> 32:54.263
I've got Mr. Landry
at 225.

32:54.300 --> 32:56.063
Auctioneer:
I thought you would.

32:56.100 --> 32:59.228
- Stop! You can't afford that.
- Charley, that's too much.

32:59.270 --> 33:00.703
Auctioneer:
60, 60, 260?

33:00.740 --> 33:03.402
How about 250? Now 60.
Go big or go home.

33:03.440 --> 33:05.271
What do you think?
250 anywhere?

33:05.310 --> 33:09.212
Once, 250 once,
250 twice...

33:09.250 --> 33:11.514
I sold it right there,
$250,000

33:11.550 --> 33:13.347
to the lady
in the red-bottom shoes.

33:13.390 --> 33:15.517
Thank you, ma'am,
we appreciate you.

33:15.560 --> 33:18.688
( people murmuring )

33:22.400 --> 33:26.166
So, can you still
buy a tractor without
breaking your budget?

33:26.200 --> 33:30.330
No, you just busted
your budget by paying
twice what you should have.

33:30.370 --> 33:33.407
Now the whole town thinks
that you got money to burn.

33:33.440 --> 33:37.228
And even worse,
that you're just a fool
that they can take for a ride.

33:37.280 --> 33:39.248
Auctioneer:
Thank you, everyone,
for joining us here today.

33:39.280 --> 33:41.817
Don't forget next week
we'll be having another auction

33:41.850 --> 33:43.647
right here
at the same place,
same time.

33:43.680 --> 33:46.547
Till then, drive safe
and be careful, now.

34:03.200 --> 34:04.701
What?

34:22.560 --> 34:26.724
( train horn blaring )

34:26.760 --> 34:29.149
Look, I can't
work for you.

34:29.200 --> 34:32.692
Now, you asked for my help,
but you didn't listen to
a word I had to say.

34:32.730 --> 34:35.733
Now, either you
don't understand
or you don't trust.

34:35.770 --> 34:38.068
Now, I'm too old
to help you, all right?

34:40.810 --> 34:42.471
Good luck.

34:48.880 --> 34:51.246
Are you here to tell me
what more I did wrong?

34:51.290 --> 34:52.382
Because I don't need--

34:52.420 --> 34:54.308
No.

34:54.360 --> 34:58.126
I'm here to tell you
all is not lost.

34:58.160 --> 35:00.321
I had a buddy of mine
win your daddy's tractor
for you

35:00.360 --> 35:03.625
after I saw you
take Landry's bait.

35:03.660 --> 35:05.719
And he got it for a song,

35:05.770 --> 35:08.637
which is the best deal
you got today.

35:20.510 --> 35:22.216
Thank you, Remy.

35:22.250 --> 35:24.241
You're welcome.

35:25.890 --> 35:29.519
But you still need
a farm manager, huh?

35:29.560 --> 35:31.551
At least you got all
the equipment you needed.

35:31.590 --> 35:33.228
I checked on delivery.

35:33.260 --> 35:35.490
It should get dropped off
in the next couple of days.

35:35.530 --> 35:37.657
( groans, laughs )

35:39.530 --> 35:41.760
Here I was,
thinking I was gonna
leave tomorrow.

35:41.800 --> 35:43.392
( laughs )

35:43.440 --> 35:46.307
I told you, farming
is serious business.

35:46.340 --> 35:49.207
You can't just dip in
and dip out.

35:49.240 --> 35:51.174
It don't work like that.

35:59.950 --> 36:01.611
Hey, everything's...

36:03.560 --> 36:05.152
What are you doing?

36:06.860 --> 36:09.795
Chef Alisa has a spread
fit for a king downstairs, man.

36:09.830 --> 36:11.969
I thought we were eating
together tonight?

36:12.000 --> 36:14.935
I'm good.
I picked up something
after hanging with Preston.

36:14.970 --> 36:17.530
Micah,

36:17.570 --> 36:19.333
we made plans to have
dinner together.

36:19.370 --> 36:22.237
This isn't cool.

36:22.280 --> 36:24.475
Micah.

36:24.510 --> 36:27.479
Fine, Dad.

36:27.510 --> 36:31.685
- Let's go eat.
- No, no, wait, wait.

36:31.720 --> 36:34.416
You're mad.
I get it.

36:34.460 --> 36:35.779
You wanna talk?

36:35.820 --> 36:38.425
No. Actually, I saw a shrink
for that, so I'm good.

36:38.460 --> 36:39.927
Hey, all right.
Listen, Micah.

36:39.960 --> 36:41.825
I still wanna
spend time With you,
all right?

36:41.860 --> 36:44.590
I wanna know what's
gomg on in your life.

36:46.300 --> 36:47.824
What happened
at the interview
with Langford?

36:47.870 --> 36:50.464
They mostly asked
about basketball,

36:50.500 --> 36:52.434
what position
I wanted to play.

36:52.470 --> 36:55.439
Oh, yeah.
What'd you say?
Point guard?

36:55.480 --> 36:57.436
Yeah,
I actually told them

36:57.480 --> 36:59.573
that I didn't want
to play anymore.

37:01.350 --> 37:04.012
What are you talking about?

37:04.050 --> 37:06.280
You love basketball.
Why'd you say that?

37:06.320 --> 37:08.686
I just don't want to.

37:08.720 --> 37:11.553
I don't even
want to be here, Dad.

37:11.590 --> 37:13.683
( phone ringing )

37:16.000 --> 37:18.992
Yeah, I gotta--
I gotta get this.

37:25.640 --> 37:27.835
Hollywood:
Feeling better?

37:27.870 --> 37:29.770
Starting to.

37:41.020 --> 37:43.011
Thank you, Hollywood.

37:43.060 --> 37:46.484
I appreciate--
I appreciate everything
you done for me.

37:46.530 --> 37:48.828
I know you do.

37:48.860 --> 37:50.725
You know I still
care for you, but--

37:50.760 --> 37:55.459
When I saw you
come to see_ me
at the hospital,

37:55.500 --> 37:57.536
it took me back

37:57.570 --> 37:58.969
to when we met.

38:00.710 --> 38:02.871
Coming in my kitchen,

38:02.910 --> 38:06.698
pretending you looking
for more of my hot water
cornbread.

38:10.980 --> 38:12.584
Yeah.

38:12.620 --> 38:14.986
I knew then,

38:15.020 --> 38:18.558
like I know now,

38:18.590 --> 38:20.820
in my heart,
we're soul mates.

38:20.860 --> 38:23.090
Leanne,
I started over.

38:23.130 --> 38:24.688
And I got a new life.

38:24.730 --> 38:26.322
You mean you got
a new woman.

38:26.370 --> 38:29.692
We both said it don't matter
what that paper say.

38:29.740 --> 38:33.836
We said that you would
let me go and move on.

38:39.610 --> 38:41.475
I had to.

38:46.920 --> 38:49.081
Please,

38:49.120 --> 38:52.021
promise me
you're gonna start taking
better care of yourself.

38:53.590 --> 38:55.990
I do take care of myself.

38:58.400 --> 39:00.721
I don't need you anyway.

39:03.500 --> 39:05.331
I don't need anyone.

39:11.480 --> 39:12.970
I called your cousin, Cora.

39:13.010 --> 39:14.716
She'll be over here
in a little while.

39:14.750 --> 39:18.709
Said she'll sit with you
for a spell.

39:18.750 --> 39:21.913
When she gets here,
everything will be
all right.

39:34.770 --> 39:36.465
Good-bye, Leanne.

39:44.810 --> 39:46.869
( ringing )

39:51.050 --> 39:52.586
Hey, how are you?

39:52.620 --> 39:54.781
It feels like
I'm in prison.

39:54.820 --> 39:57.516
We're surrounded
by paparazzi.

39:57.560 --> 39:59.551
Mom, I can't go
back to school.

39:59.590 --> 40:01.080
And I see Stella everywhere.

40:01.130 --> 40:03.553
Maybe we can get a tutor
or something, but--

40:03.600 --> 40:05.693
No, baby.

40:05.730 --> 40:07.061
A tutor isn't the answer.

40:07.100 --> 40:10.729
What we need
is a fresh start.

40:10.770 --> 40:12.829
You know,
I was thinking,

40:12.870 --> 40:15.532
we could temporarily
move to St. Josephine.

40:15.580 --> 40:17.502
Just-- just for
the rest of the year.

40:17.540 --> 40:19.542
Yeah.

40:19.580 --> 40:21.104
Sure, whatever.
Okay.

40:21.150 --> 40:22.970
Really?

40:23.020 --> 40:25.545
So, you're okay with that?

40:27.720 --> 40:29.881
Anywhere but here.

40:31.560 --> 40:33.755
I'm on it.

40:33.790 --> 40:35.599
Talk later?

40:35.630 --> 40:36.949
Talk later.

40:40.500 --> 40:42.468
( phone rings )

40:44.240 --> 40:45.537
Micah?

40:45.570 --> 40:48.505
It's Melina...
Galoudian.

40:50.980 --> 40:53.073
You asked me
what I wanted.

40:55.750 --> 40:57.843
I'm listening.

40:59.190 --> 41:01.146
I want $3 million.

41:05.590 --> 41:07.057
Wow.

41:07.090 --> 41:10.025
And I want a face-to-face
sit-down with Davis.

41:10.060 --> 41:12.995
I want him to admit
what he did to me.

41:14.940 --> 41:17.158
Well, I'll have
to talk that over

41:17.200 --> 41:19.668
with our attorney.

41:19.710 --> 41:21.871
It's not negotiable.

41:24.710 --> 41:26.803
And if we do this,

41:26.850 --> 41:28.841
will this be
the end of it?

41:30.580 --> 41:32.081
Yes.

41:35.660 --> 41:36.888
Fine.

41:38.120 --> 41:41.226
Then we'll see you
in Houston

41:41.260 --> 41:43.194
for one last time.

41:56.880 --> 41:59.599
- ( music playing )
- ( women vocalizing )
